SIMPLE: flighty
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flighty
<hw>Flight"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Fleeting;
swift; transient.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>flighty</qex> purpose never is o'ertook,⟦br⟧
Unless the deed go with it.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Indulging in flights, or wild and unrestrained
sallies, of imagination, humor, caprice, etc.; given to disordered
fancies and extravagant conduct; volatile; giddy; eccentric; slightly
delirious.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Proofs of my <qex>flighty</qex> and paradoxical turn of mind.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A harsh disciplinarian and a <qex>flighty</qex> enthusiast.</q>
<rj><qau>J. S. Harford.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flimflam</ent>⟦br⟧
